    "last_edit_date" : 1465295477,
    "creation_date" : 1246397985,
    "answer_id" : 1066223,
    "question_id" : 1062941,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You want a <code>.jardesc</code> file. They do not kick off automatically, but it's within 2 clicks.</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Right click on your project</li>\n<li>Choose <code>Export &gt; Java &gt; JAR file</code></li>\n<li>Choose included files and name output JAR, then click <code>Next</code></li>\n<li>Check \"Save the description of this JAR in the workspace\" and choose a name for the new <code>.jardesc</code> file</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Now, all you have to do is right click on your <code>.jardesc</code> file and choose <code>Create JAR</code> and it will export it in the same spot.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 257905,
      "reputation" : 782,
