    "answer_id" : 9069866,
    "question_id" : 1062941,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Regarding to Peter's answer and Micheal's addition to it you may find <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1119677/how-do-i-automatically-generate-a-jar-file-in-an-eclipse-java-project\">How Do I Automatically Generate A .jar File In An Eclipse Java Project</a> useful. Because even you have \"*.jardesc\" file on your project you have to run it manually. It may cools down your \"eclipse click hassle\" a bit.</p>\n"
