      "body" : "After having tried both, this solution seems much better than Konrad&#39;s. It requires you to manually figure out some paths in your build file but it allows automatic build (instead of 2 clicks) and allow for easy customization (copy the jar after build for example).  Here&#39;s how to build a jar file when having the build file in the root and having multiple nested levels of packages: <code>&lt;jar jarfile=&quot;dist&#47;mypackage.jar&quot; basedir=&quot;bin&#47;&quot; includes=&quot;**&#47;*.class&quot; &#47;&gt;</code>"
