    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1446218265,
    "creation_date" : 1446218265,
    "answer_id" : 33439315,
    "question_id" : 1062941,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Using <strong>Thomas Bratt</strong>'s answer above, just make sure your build.xml is configured properly :</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" ?&gt;\n&lt;!-- Configuration of the Ant build system to generate a Jar file --&gt; \n&lt;project name=\"TestMain\" default=\"CreateJar\"&gt;\n  &lt;target name=\"CreateJar\" description=\"Create Jar file\"&gt;\n        &lt;jar jarfile=\"Test.jar\" basedir=\"bin/\" includes=\"**/*.class\" /&gt;\n  &lt;/target&gt;\n&lt;/project&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>(Notice the <strong>double asterisk</strong> - it will tell build to look for .class files in all sub-directories.)</p>\n"
